               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310407-210-person1524">
                  PHOEBE 
                  READ
               <interp inst="t18310407-210-person1524" type="surname" value="READ"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-210-person1524" type="given" value="PHOEBE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-210-person1524" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in White Lion-yard, and am a shoe-maker. I have known the prisoner about three years- in February last he gave me two pairs of boot-tops to sell for him; I gave them to King, the officer.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. CLARKSON. Q. Did you buy them yourself? A. No - I never knew any harm of him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310407-210-person1525">
                  JOHN 
                  READ
               <interp inst="t18310407-210-person1525" type="surname" value="READ"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-210-person1525" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-210-person1525" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am the last witness' husband. The prisoner left two other pairs of boot-tops with me to sell; I did not sell them, but gave them to King.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Do you recollect when this was? A. Two or three days before the officer came, and a day or two after he left the two with my wife.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18310407-210-person1526">
                  JOHN 
                  THOMAS
               <interp inst="t18310407-210-person1526" type="surname" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-210-person1526" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18310407-210-person1526" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             KING. I am an officer. I received four pairs of boot-tops from Read.</p>
               <p>ROWLAND SWAN. I am a serjeant of the Police. I saw the prisoner at the station-house; he said he did not deny taking the property - I searched his room, and found some leather.</p>
               <p>ABRAHAM NORTHEN. I am a shoe-maker, and live in King-street, Smithfield. The prisoner has worked for me ten years; I missed four pairs of boot-tops on the 22nd or<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183104070102"></xptr>24th of February - these are them; they are called boottops in the trade.</p>
               <p>
